Basics
	Video cards generate and Output images to a display
	Video is defined by
		Display modes
		Motherboard slot
		GPU (integrated vs separate)
		Video memory
		Connections
	Video card Contains 
		Video Circuitry
			Evolved into specialized GPU
			ATI and NVIDIA make most GPUs
		Memory
			Typically faster than system RAM
			DDR, DDR2, GDDR3/4/5

--------------------------------------------
Modes
	Text Mode (typically monochrome, used by BIOS)
		80 characters x 24 rows = 1920 Bytes
	Graphics Mode
		Monochrome
		Fixed Color (2-16 bits per pixel)
		Palette (8 bits per pixel / 24 bit Palette)
			VGA 640 x 480 = 307KB
		Deep Color (24+ bits per pixel)
			1920 x 1080 x 3 = 6,220,800 Bytes
--------------------------------------------
Busses / Expansion Slots
	PCI
		adequate for general use
		Bandwidth is shared for all devices on bus
		Video often requires more bandwidth
	AGP (obsolete)
		Dedicated to Video
		2x, 4x, 8x flavors
		2-16 times faster then PCI
	PCIe-16
		2-8 times faster then AGP 8x
	Integrated
		GPU built-in to CPU

