Monitor Connections
	VGA (RGB, DSub-15)  [[img http://www.crs-uk.biz/images/vga_dvi_card.jpg]]
		Called HD15 by CompTIA
		15 pins, in three rows
		Analog signal, Optimal for CRTs
	DVI (Digital Video Interface) [[img images/DVI_Connectors.png]]
			DVI-A - analog
			DVI-D - digital
			DVI-I - integrated (both) [[img images/DMS_59.jpg]]
			Single link and Dual Link versions
	DisplayPort
		Supports higher bandwidth than HDMI [[img images/VideoConnectors.png]]
		Manufacturers can use it "royalty free" (HDMI requires royalties)
	Thunderbolt
	DMS-59 typically offers two DVI connectors 
	CompTIA includes ethernet RJ-45 as a video cable
------------------------------------------
Monitor Connections (consumer)
	HDMI (High-Definition Multimedia Interface) [[img images/DVI_HDMI_DisplayPort.jpg]]
		Loosely described as: Single-link DVI + Audio
		Associated software includes HDCP (high-def Content Protection)
	For other video devices [[img images/VideoAdapters.jpg]]
		[[S-Video!http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/S-Video]] 
		[[Composite!http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/RCA_connector]] (RCA port)
		[[Others!http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_display_interfaces]]
	RCA - Composite Video
	SVideo - Mini-DIN, called miniDIN6 by CompTIA
	BNC - Often used with component video
	An adapter can sometimes be used to convert from one type to another (but not always)
